There are multiple ways to embed a PDF file on a website. You can use third-party services like DocSend or Google Drive, or you can embed the PDF file directly using HTML or JavaScript. Here are a few methods:

1. Using an iframe:
```html
<iframe src="https://example.com/your-pdf-file.pdf" width="100%" height="500px" frameborder="0"></iframe>
```
Replace `https://example.com/your-pdf-file.pdf` with the URL of your PDF file.

1. Using Google Drive:
* Upload your PDF file to Google Drive.
* Right-click the file and choose "Get link" or "Share."
* Set the permissions to "Anyone with the link."
* Click "Copy link."
* Replace `https://drive.google.com/file/d/FILE_ID/view?usp=sharing` in the following code with the link you just copied:
```html
<iframe src="https://drive.google.com/file/d/FILE_ID/preview" width="100%" height="500px" frameborder="0"></iframe>
```
1. Using DocSend:
* Sign up for a DocSend account and upload your PDF file.
* Set the appropriate sharing settings for your document.
* Copy the shareable link provided by DocSend.
* Replace `https://docsend.com/view/DOCSEND_ID` in the following code with the link you just copied:
```html
<iframe src="https://docsend.com/view/DOCSEND_ID" width="100%" height="500px" frameborder="0"></iframe>
```
1. Using JavaScript libraries:

There are JavaScript libraries like PDF.js (by Mozilla) that enable you to embed PDF files on your website. To use PDF.js, follow these steps:

* Download and include the PDF.js library in your project. You can find it at <https://mozilla.github.io/pdf.js/>.
* Use the following HTML code to create a container for your PDF file:
```html
<div id="pdf-container" style="width: 100%; height: 500px;"></div>
```
* Add the following JavaScript code to load and render the PDF file:
```javascript
pdfjsLib.getDocument('https://example.com/your-pdf-file.pdf').promise.then(function(pdf) {
  pdf.getPage(1).then(function(page) {
    var scale = 1;
    var viewport = page.getViewport({ scale: scale });
    var container = document.getElementById('pdf-container');
    container.width = viewport.width;
    container.height = viewport.height;

    var canvas = document.createElement('canvas');
    container.appendChild(canvas);

    var context = canvas.getContext('2d');
    canvas.width = viewport.width;
    canvas.height = viewport.height;

    var renderContext = {
      canvasContext: context,
      viewport: viewport,
    };

    page.render(renderContext);
  });
});
```
Replace `https://example.com/your-pdf-file.pdf` with the URL of your PDF file.

Remember that embedding a large PDF file might affect your website's performance. It's a good idea to optimize your PDF files and consider offering a download link for users who prefer to download the file instead of viewing it in their browser.

