Here's a script in MATLAB that writes out the path and file names of a given directory to a text file:
```vbnet
function write_directory_info(dir_path, text_file_path)
% Write the path and file names of the directory to a text file
%
% Inputs:
%   dir_path - The path of the directory
%   text_file_path - The path of the text file to write the information to
%
% Example:
%   write_directory_info('/path/to/dir', '/path/to/file.txt')

% Get the list of files and directories in the given directory
files = dir(dir_path);

% Open the text file for writing
fid = fopen(text_file_path, 'w');

% Write the header
fprintf(fid, 'Name\t\t\t\t\tType\t\tPath\n');

% Loop through each file and write its information to the text file
for i = 1:length(files)
    % Get the file information
    file = files(i);
    name = file.name;
    type = '';
    if file.isdir
        type = 'Directory';
    else
        type = 'File';
    end
    path = fullfile(dir_path, name);

    % Write the information to the text file
    fprintf(fid, '%s\t\t%s\t\t%s\n', name, type, path);
end

% Close the text file
fclose(fid);
end
